<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-01-12T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-01-12T05:00:00-05:00" n="228" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d228">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.811/240</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Reinsch</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-01-12T18:00:00+08:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 12, 1917, 6
                                p.m</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your telegram of January 8, 5 p.m.<note n="31" xml:id="d228fn31">Printed
                                under Huai River and Grand Canal conservancy project, <ref target="#pg_207">p. 207</ref>.</note> I have informally
                            suggested to Japanese Minister possibility of cooperation between
                            American and Japanese interests in the construction of railways in
                            Manchuria recalling to him the existence of American rights in that
                            regard.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>